"decision_summary": "The RequireFullyCanonicalSig amendment enhances ledger security by eliminating transaction malleability for single-signed transactions. Given that Ripple's utilities have been compliant since 2014 and most utilities enable this by default, the ecosystem is well-prepared. While there is a minor risk to legacy non-compliant utilities and multi-sig malleability remains, the security benefits and high level of existing compliance justify a YES vote.",
